# Introduction

Welcome to one of the most important topics in JavaScript.

Everything you've learned so far has prepared you for this moment.

Until now you've learned how to:

- create elements
- remove elements
- update elements
- modify attributes
- manipulate classes
- build interfaces

But something important has been missing...

Your applications cannot **react**.

Imagine building:

- a calculator
- a login form
- WhatsApp
- Facebook
- YouTube
- Gmail
- Google Docs
- Spotify

Without users interacting with them.

Impossible.

A webpage without events is like:

- a television that cannot receive a remote signal
- a car whose steering wheel doesn't work
- a phone whose touchscreen doesn't respond

Everything exists...

Nothing responds.

DOM Events solve this problem.

