# Browser and JavaScript Relationship

Many beginners think JavaScript controls the browser.

Actually...

The browser controls JavaScript much more than people realize.

The browser is the operating environment.

Think of the browser as the manager.

JavaScript is an employee.

The browser decides:

- when scripts run
- when pages load
- when events occur
- when rendering happens
- when repainting happens

JavaScript simply responds.

---

# Browser Responsibilities

The browser:

- paints pages
- downloads resources
- builds the DOM
- creates CSSOM
- calculates layouts
- detects clicks
- detects scrolling
- detects touches
- detects keyboard input
- detects window resize
- detects page visibility
- creates events

JavaScript performs calculations when the browser asks it to.

